===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} – a street intersection. Original form of {{och-l|行|id=1|place}}. Later {{Han phonetically borrowed}} to represent {{och-l|行|id=2|to go}}.

Originally symmetric, it has been simplified asymmetrically; the left half {{l|zh|彳}} is widely used as a radical, while the right half {{l|zh|亍}} finds occasional use, and the character can be broken up as {{Han compound|彳|亍}}, though originally it was not a compound.

===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} tentatively considers the word to be {{bor+|zh|mkh|-|nocap=1}}; compare {{cog|km|រង|t=ridge, gutter}}. Note also similarities to {{cog|my|ကျင့်|t=to practice}} ({{zh-ref|Luce, 1981}}).

